23/03/2008
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- The parliament ratified on Friday (March 21st) the Lisbon Treaty, which replaced the EU constitution project.
The European Commission (EC) expressed satisfaction with Bulgaria's decision to approve the document.
In an official statement, EC President Jose Manuel Barroso said he highly values the early approval of the agreement.
He is due to arrive in Bulgaria next week to assess the country's progress and ways to improve co-operation with Bulgarian authorities.
(Trud - 22/03/08;
News.bg, AP, BTA, BNR - 21/03/08)
